                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d203">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">715.1715/1386: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Representative of the President</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Corrigan</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-01-24T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 24, 1939—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>7. Your telegram of January 20, No. 8, 3 p.m. There is no objection to your plan
                    for the Commission to meet in Panama upon the arrival there of Dr. Zúñiga
                    Montúfar.</p>
                <p>Careful consideration will be given to the suggestion contained in the second
                    sentence of the last paragraph of your telegram.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
